  titleNative: "बाज़ार में ख़रीदारी",
  focus: "Learn shopping phrases for markets in Jaipur, Delhi, and Varanasi. You will ask prices, sizes, colors, and bargain politely.",
  vocab: [{ hi: "दुकान", en: "shop", ipa: "dʊ-kaːn" }, { hi: "दुकानदार", en: "shopkeeper", ipa: "dʊ-kaːn-daːr" }, { hi: "कीमत", en: "price", ipa: "kiː-mət" }, { hi: "महँगा", en: "expensive", ipa: "mə-həŋ-gaː" }, { hi: "सस्ता", en: "cheap / inexpensive", ipa: "səs-taː" }, { hi: "रंग", en: "color", ipa: "rəŋg" }, { hi: "आकार", en: "size", ipa: "aː-kaːr" }, { hi: "कपड़ा", en: "cloth / clothing", ipa: "kəp-ɽaː" }, { hi: "जूते", en: "shoes", ipa: "dʒuː-teː" }, { hi: "बैग", en: "bag", ipa: "bɛːg" }],
  phrases: [{ hi: "यह कितने का है?", en: "How much is this?", ipa: "jəh kɪt-neː kaː hɛː" }, { hi: "यह बहुत महँगा है।", en: "This is very expensive.", ipa: "jəh bə-hʊt mə-həŋ-gaː hɛː" }, { hi: "कुछ सस्ता है?", en: "Is there something cheaper?", ipa: "kʊtʃʰ səs-taː hɛː" }, { hi: "मुझे यह रंग पसंद है।", en: "I like this color.", ipa: "mʊ-dʒʰeː jəh rəŋg pə-sənd hɛː" }, { hi: "क्या बड़ा आकार है?", en: "Is there a larger size?", ipa: "kjaː bə-ɽaː aː-kaːr hɛː" }, { hi: "मैं यह लूँगा।", en: "I will take this.", ipa: "mɛːn jəh luːŋ-gaː" }],
  grammar: "पसंद है means “like.” Hindi often phrases this as “to me, this color is liked”: मुझे यह रंग पसंद है. Use मुझे ... पसंद है for food, clothes, places, and people.",
